  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bca\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bb2\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0baf \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0bc0.\u0b8e\u0bb2\u0bcd.\u0baa\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Minister GL Peiris briefing the Commonwealth Foreign Ministers on the state of the country",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Following the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting (CHOGM), Foreign Minister Prof. GL Peiris met with Foreign Ministers and senior officials of various countries to brief them on the current economic crisis in the country and the international cooperation required to recover from it.",
        "As a side event of the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting (CHOGM) in Rwanda on the 24th and 25th, Sri Lankan Minister of Foreign Affairs Prof. GL Peiris met with the Heads of the Commonwealth Foreign Ministers' and High Level Committees on the political and economic crisis currently facing the country, the recovery from this crisis and the diversification of infrastructure. Discussed matters with them.",
        "Accordingly, Minister of Foreign Affairs, International Trade and Relations with the Diaspora Dominica Kenneth met with Trox during the meeting to discuss tourism activities that are essential for both countries.",
        "They also shared the experiences of both the countries in rescuing the tourism industry which was badly affected by the Corona virus outbreak.",
        "Expansion of maritime cooperation was discussed during a meeting with Sylvester Radekont, Minister of Foreign Affairs and Tourism in the Seychelles.",
        "Bangladesh Minister of Foreign Affairs AK Abdul Momen briefed Minister GL Peiris on the steps being taken to assist Sri Lanka, which is facing an economic crisis, by providing assistance including food and medicine, as well as loans.",
        "Also present were Kenya's Foreign Ministry Secretary Rachel Omamo, Mauritius' Minister of Foreign Affairs, Regional Relations and International Trade Alan Kano, Cypriot Foreign Minister Lonis Casolidis, Malaysian Foreign Minister Saifuddin Abdullah, Rwanda's Foreign Minister and Foreign Minister. , Explained the current situation in the country, various issues including the progress made in the reconciliation process."
      ],
